Market Definition

Water testing is a method of determining water quality. Water quality must be monitored on a regular basis in order to assess its health. Water testing and analysis are used to determine turbidity, dissolved gas concentration, radioactivity, and water conductivity. Water purity is critical to many industries and activities, including agriculture, fisheries, electronics, food, pharmaceutical aquaculture, and forestry. Water testing is classified into two types: physiochemical testing and bacteriological testing.



